14 a. Five hundred dollars ($500) for the first offense;
15 b. One thousand dollars ($1,000) for the second offense within a one
16 (1) year period; and
17 c. Two thousand dollars ($2,000) for any subsequent offense within a
18 one (1) year period.
19 The Transportation Cabinet shall erect signs warning drivers of the
20 increased fines in this subparagraph. Signs erected under this
21 subparagraph shall be placed in such a manner that drivers are given
22 adequate warning in order to exit the road prior to crossing the bridge. If
23 warning signs are not erected in accordance with this subparagraph, the
24 fines in this subparagraph shall not apply and violators shall be fined
25 under subparagraph 1. of this paragraph.
